Replace the `const short int inputlinelength = 1024;` declaration with a
`#define`. GCC and Clang fold the const-int to a constant for the
`char inputline[inputlinelength];` stack-array size at line 107, but
MSVC strictly requires a C constant expression and does not implement
C99 VLAs as a fallback. Upstream's TL Windows build avoids the issue
by cross-compiling with MinGW gcc instead of MSVC.

--- a/utils/ps2eps/ps2eps-src/src/C/bbox.c
+++ b/utils/ps2eps/ps2eps-src/src/C/bbox.c
@@ -56,7 +56,7 @@ const char *const version= "$Rev: 146 $";
 const char *const prgname= "bbox";

 const double round_precision= 1e-6;
-const short int inputlinelength= 1024;
+#define inputlinelength 1024

 unsigned char bitval[8]=
